The paper proposes a two-tiered architecture for solving visual arithmetic tasks using deep neural networks and reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks and reinforcement learning for coordination and control suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing and symbolic transformations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
